         <OBJECT_CONTRACT ITEM="1">
            <TITLE>
               <P>Denbighshire County Council Residential Care Home and Day Centre Supplier Engagement Event</P>
            </TITLE>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="85300000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Denbighshire County Council is modernising all of its in-house care services. Following a consultation, the Council seeks an innovative and progressive partner to take over the running of our 30 bedded care home in Denbigh. Whilst we are currently registered to provide residential care, we are looking for a partner to develop the building to deliver quality Elderly mental health (EMH) residential and day care on the site.</P>
               <P>An experienced and well trained council team presently support 24 residents and 14 in day care. The Council has made a commitment to continue to provide care and support for the current service users whilst any development is taking place.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="85300000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKL13"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The Council would like to invite providers with experience in running a registered EMH residential care home to discuss these plans further.</P>
                  <P>Partners for this project will demonstrate a clear vision for the development of the site, with a focus on promoting independence and well-being. Partners would share the vision to maintain social care values, including the Welsh language and culture and continue the positive relationships with the local community.</P>
                  <P>This is an exciting opportunity for a provider with expertise and a proven track record in providing a similar service, to run and transform a well-established and valued residential home, with skilled and experienced staff.</P>
                  <P>The commissioned provider will continue to deliver high quality support for older people in a homely environment, offering value for money and delivering outcomes to meet the needs of the community.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
            <DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>2018-05-31</DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <LEFTI/>
         <COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
            <INFO_ADD>
               <P>Providers are invited to an event to discuss this opportunity. The event will be supported by Council members, Executive officers and Community support services staff.</P>
               <P>The event will take place on Monday May 14th 10am to 12.30pm at Dolwen Care Home, Denbigh, LL16 3ER.</P>
               <P>If you would like to attend the event please email alison.heaton@denbighshire.gov.uk Please note that attendance is strictly limited to 2 representatives from each organisation.</P>
               <P>The Council welcomes collaborative proposals and approaches from social enterprises. This notice forms the beginning of a dialogue with potential partners.</P>
               <P>(WA Ref:81118).</P>
            </INFO_ADD>
            <DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE>2018-04-19</DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE>
         </COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
      </F21_2014>
